      • compareIntArrayAndMask

        public static boolean compareIntArrayAndMask(int[] array1,
                                             boolean[] array2)
        Utility method comparing a bootstrap against mask positions to check that only (mask==true) sites are selected.

        NB not entirely guaranteed to be safe since it drops to false if sampled sites (bootstrap[i]>0) are in the mask's boolean array. Since even valid sites might not get sampled, especially for big alignments, this test might miss some.

        Parameters:
        array1 -
        array2 -
        Returns:
